data.enText: the process of growing physically, mentally or emotionally
Lack of water will stunt the plant's growth.

data.chText: 去掉枯叶以促进新叶生长。
data.enText: Remove dead leaves to encourage new growth.

data.chText: 对个人成长和发展的重视
data.enText: a concern with personal (= mental and emotional) growth and development
growth hormones (= designed to make sb/sth grow faster)
an increase in the size, amount or degree of sth
the rapid growth in violent crime

data.chText: 英美经济增长无几、令人沮丧的一年
data.enText: a disappointing year of little growth in Britain and America

data.chText: 旨在保持经济增长的政策
data.enText: policies aimed at sustaining economic growth

data.chText: 经济增长的领域 / 行业

data.enText: a lump caused by a disease that forms on or inside a person, an animal or a plant

data.chText: 森林里茂密的植物为各种各样的鸟儿提供了筑巢的地方。
data.enText: The forest's dense growth provides nesting places for a wide variety of birds.

simple_means.memory_skill: grow 成长 + th 行为，状态 → 成长

ex.chText: 现在有许多种癌症可以治愈。
ex.enText: A lot of cancers can now be cured.
My dog has a canker sore in its mouth.

synonyms.bx: 指花木的枝枯病，也指人和动物的溃疡病。

ex.chText: 他喉咙处上长了一个肿块。
ex.enText: He has a growth on his throat.

synonyms.bx: 指人、动物或植物体表或体内因病变而长出的肿块。

ex.chText: 外科医生给她做手术以切除肿瘤。
ex.enText: The surgeon operated on her to remove the tumour.

ex.chText: 医生认为这个肿块是良性的。
ex.enText: The doctor diagnosed the tumour as benign.

synonyms.bx: 指人或动物身体某部位因病变而长出且迅速增大的肿块。

tr: the gradual beginning or coming forth
example: figurines presage the emergence of sculpture in Greece
the only growth was some salt grass

tr: (biology) the process of an individual organism growing organically
a purely biological unfolding of events involved in an organism changing gradually from a simple to a more complex level
example: he proposed an indicator of osseous development in children

tr: a progression from simpler to more complex forms
a process of becoming larger or longer or more numerous or more important
(pathology) an abnormal proliferation of tissue (as in a tumor)

value.def: The growth of something such as an industry, organization, or idea is its development in size, wealth, or importance.
The growth in something is the increase in it.

example.ex: A steady growth in the popularity of two smaller parties may upset the polls...
example.tran: 两个较小政党的支持率稳步上升，可能会打乱投票结果。

example.ex: The area has seen a rapid population growth...
The market has shown annual growth of 20 per cent for several years.
example.tran: 这几年的市场年增长率都保持在20%。

gramarinfo.label: also <l>a</l> N, oft supp N, N <l>in</l> n, N <l>of</l> amount

value.def: A growth industry, area, or market is one which is increasing in size or activity.

example.ex: Computers and electronics are growth industries and need skilled technicians...
example.tran: 计算机与电子行业属于蓬勃发展的产业，需要娴熟的技术人员。

example.ex: Real estate lending has become the biggest growth area for American banks.
example.tran: 房地产贷款已经成了美国银行业增长最快的业务领域。

value.def: Someone's growth is the development and progress of their character.

example.tran: 孩子的情感与智力发展

example.ex: Different teachers make different contributions to a student's growth.
example.tran: 不同的教师在学生的成长过程中起到不同的作用。

value.def: Growth in a person, animal, or plant is the process of increasing in physical size and development.

example.ex: ...hormones which control fertility and body growth...
example.tran: 控制生殖和身体发育的荷尔蒙

example.ex: Cells divide and renew as part of the human growth process.
example.tran: 细胞不断地分裂更新，这是人体发育过程的一部分。

value.def: You can use growth to refer to plants which have recently developed or which developed at the same time.

example.ex: This helps to ripen new growth and makes it flower profusely...
example.tran: 这有助于新生发植株的成熟，令其开出繁茂的花朵。

example.ex: Pinch out the tips of the young growths to make for compact, bushy plants.
example.tran: 掐掉幼株的芽尖以便让它们长得紧凑浓密，呈丛生状。

value.tran: 新生发的植株；一茬植株

value.def: A growth is a lump that grows inside or on a person, animal, or plant, and that is caused by a disease.

example.ex: This type of surgery could even be used to extract cancerous growths.
example.tran: 这种外科手术甚至可以用来切除癌性肿瘤。

trans: (树木、贝壳或骨等的)生长轮，年轮
(尤用于治疗儿童矮小症的)人体生长激素(缩略形式为HGH)

meanings.td: 表名词，通常指抽象名词，“行为，性质，状态”
